abstract: DEERFIELD BEACH, Fla., Feb. 3 (UPI)--JoAnne Carner shrugged off the wind, the cold and a rival, Sandra Post, today as she shot an even-par 73 to win the $15,000 first prize in the Championship of Deer Creek, the first event on the 1980 Ladies' Professional Golf Association tour.
headline_main: Mrs. Carner Takes L.P.G.A. Event by 2; 2 Double Bogeys

abstract: DEERFIELD BEACH, Fla., Feb. 2, (UPI)--Beth Daniel, the 1979 rookie of the year, made three birdies and an eagle on her final four holes today to finish with a 67 and tie JoAnne Carner for the lead after three rounds of the first stop on the 1980 Ladies' Professional Golf Association tour.
headline_main: Miss Daniel, at 209, Ties for Lead in Golf; Miss Lopez at 222 A Success Story

abstract: DEERFIELD BEACH, Fla., Feb. 1 (AP)--JoAnne Carner survived temperatures in the 60's and 35-mile-anhour gusts today to shoot a one-underpar 70 that vaulted her into the secondround lead of the $100,000 season-opening tournament on the Ladies' Professional Golf Association tour.

SOUTH SALEM, N.Y. TUCKED away in a converted general store in this rural town, seven women spend their days in an uncommon pursuit:  the preservation of textiles. But the Textile Conservation Workshop on Main Street is unusual because the skills practiced there are available to the general public.
